headline: Why GoDaddy Stock Crashed Today
summary: Shares of website company GoDaddy (NYSE: GDDY) crashed on Friday after the company released its financial results for the fourth quarter of 2024.  As of 12:50 p.m. ET, GoDaddy stock was down about 13%.  For Q4, GoDaddy expected to grow revenue by only about 7% year over year, but it wound up growing by 8% to $1.2 billion.
